  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A person in this role leads a group of developers in the task of the development of a security architecture. A security&#xD;
    architecture is a representation of the best practices of the security community. It often includes the selection of&#xD;
    preferred security patterns for system design (&lt;i>security design patterns&lt;/i>), the documentation of technical policy&#xD;
    (&lt;i>policy design patterns&lt;/i>) concerning security implementation &lt;i>(security implementation patterns&lt;/i>) and&#xD;
    &lt;i>security architectural patterns&lt;/i>, thereby reflecting the key technical decisions that constrain the overall&#xD;
    security implementation for the project.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
